Title: Series: Beatae intacta semper Virginis Mariae
Description: The Flight into Egypt: in the foreground, the Virgin and Christ child ride on a donkey, Joseph follows on foot, an ox accompanies the group; to the far left, reapers appear in a cornfield, Herod's soldiers approach; within ornamental frame. c.1589 Engraving
Producer name: Print made by: Jan Collaert II
Curator's comments: For comment on the series see Nn,7.4.4.
